    <Folder>
      <name>Intelligence Summary</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>AI Council Assessment</name>
        <styleUrl>#intel</styleUrl>
        <description>The synthesized intelligence assessment reveals a U.S. military posture characterized by routine training, ISR expansion, and sustained naval deployments with no immediate indicators of crisis response. The USAF maintains a robust training and reconnaissance footprint across CONUS and overseas, with notable platforms including T-6 Texan IIs, C-130s, and Learjets conducting local and regional missions. The presence of a Boeing 767 (IAM1427) over Italy and an Airbus A330 (MMF34) over Alaska suggests ongoing diplomatic and logistical support for European and Indo-Pacific operations. The Embraer E-390 (ZEUS58) over Brazil indicates expanded ISR coverage in the South Atlantic, while the C-30J Spartan (C2009) over Hawaii supports Pacific theater logistics. Naval activity is concentrated on the USS Gerald R. Ford (CVN-78), which is post-repair transit from Croatia, and the USS Rushmore (LSD-47), actively transiting the Strait of Malacca to reinforce U.S. Central Command. The overall pattern reflects a deliberate, non-escalatory military presence with a focus on regional stability, training readiness, and sustained power projection capabilities. No unusual or anomalous activity patterns were detected in the combined dataset.</description>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>0,0,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
